title: Midseason report: Best, worst of college football's 1st half
text: > Top News Midseason report: Best, worst of college football's 1st half FILE - In this Oct. 11, 2014, file photo, North Texas head coach Dan McCarney looks on near the end of their 56-21 loss to UAB in an NCAA college football game at Legion Field in Birmingham, Ala. North Texas fired Dan McCarney right after the Mean Green were hammered on homecoming 66-7 by FCS Portland State. It was clear even going into the game that the end was approaching for McCarney, but athletic director Rick Villareal did not even let the coach hold a postgame news conference. (AP Photo/Al.com/Hal Yeager, File)
